mention.text: the dead Christ between the living thieves
The congregation of the dead make room
thee , who so long ago Filled thy young heart with passion and the woe From which thy song and all its splendors came
thy young heart with passion and the woe
makest full confession ; and a gleam
holy men who died , Here martyred and hereafter glorified
O bringer of the light , whose splendor shines Above the darkness of the Apennines , Forerunner of the day that is to be !
